description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CDD Services is a wholly owned subsidiary of County Durham and Darlington NHS Foundation Trust (CDDFT) set up to deliver a range of non-clinical Estates, Facilities and Procurement services across the Trust. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CDDFT are one of the largest integrated care providers in England serving a population of around 650,000 people. Acute hospital services are provided at Darlington Memorial Hospital and University Hospital of North Durham and Bishop Auckland Hospital is a centre for planned care. Community services are provided from six community hospitals alongside eighty other community based locations. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CDD Services’ Inventory Management team is responsible for the ordering, stock control, receipt and distribution of more than £25m of medical supplies into 3 major CDDFT hospitals and 58 further healthcare locations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join CDD Services’ Inventory Management team working in Theatre Stores at University Hospital of North Durham. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be a well-motivated, outgoing, conscientious person to join our Theatre Stores team. Reporting to the Theatre Stores Team Leader, you will be responsible for ordering and receiving goods into Theatres at University Hospital of North Durham.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To apply for the Theatre Storekeeper role you must have purchasing and/or procurement knowledge (preferably in a Theatre stores setting), hold NVQ level 3 (in an appropriate subject) and be willing to work towards NVQ Level 4 or have equivalent experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
